article.headline: Sacramento St. 74, William Jessup 42
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. -- Justin Eller had 14 points and eight rebounds Monday as Sacramento State beat William Jessup 74-42. Domineek Daniel added 10 points for the Hornets (6-7), who shot 58 percent (30 for 51) from the floor compared to just 25 percent (15 of 60) for William Jessup. Kadeem Kirsten had 14 points to lead William Jessup (3-10), an NAIA school. Sacramento State made its first four 3-pointers and led by 22 points with 5:31 left in the first half. The Hornets led 39-23 at the half and 50-34 with 12 minutes remaining before slowly building their 32-point margin.
